This paper proposes a method for generating contrastive explanations for any classification model, including deep neural networks, random forests, and boosted trees. The paper focuses on structured data and proposes a principled approach to handle real and categorical features. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
